Package com.pacman.game

Class Summary
BlinkyGhost This class implements the chase pattern of Blinky, the red ghost.
ClydeGhost This class implements the chase pattern of Clyde, the orange ghost.
Ghost This abstract class implements all the different states of a ghost.
InkyGhost This class implements the chase pattern of Inky, the blue ghost.
Level This class holds all the information specific to a certain level, such as the maze layout and the speeds of the objects.
Maze This is the Maze class that holds all the tiles of the maze.
MovableObject This class defines a basic object that is placed on the maze, and that is always aligned to the gridlines of the maze.
Pacman This implements the Pacman class.
PinkyGhost This class implements the chase pattern of Pinky, the pink ghost.
Tile This class will represent a single tile on the Maze.
Vector2 Class representing a 2d vector of floats with many helper methods for easy vector manipulations and math.
Vector2I Class representing a 2d vector of ints with many helper methods for easy vector manipulations and math.
World The world class.
 

Enum Summary
Ghost.GhostState The state of a Ghost.
MovableObject.Direction Direction with some helper methods to convert between vectors and direction enums
Tile.Type These are the different types of tiles we can have.
World.GameState State of the game
